-- Market Chatter- Corporate finance press digest
-- 
-- Fri Jul 25, 2014 12:13AM EDT
-- None



July 25 (Reuters) - The following corporate finance-related stories were reported by media:

* U.S. cable group Liberty Global <LBTYA.O> has offered to sell its pay TV channel Film1 in an attempt to win EU antitrust approval for its proposed acquisition of Dutch rival Ziggo <ZIGGO.AS>, a person familiar with the matter said on Thursday. [ID:nL6N0PZ5KW]  * The board of Italy's flagship airline Alitalia will propose to shareholders a capital increase of as much as 250 million euros ($336.68 million), a source with knowledge of a document said on Thursday after a meeting of the airline's board. [ID:nL6N0PZ74S]  * The long-awaited fine on Britain's Lloyds Banking Group <LLOY.L> in relation to the benchmark interest rate (LIBOR) fixing allegations will be announced next week, two sources familiar with the inquiry told Reuters. [ID:nL2N0PZ2YC]  * U.S. real estate website operator Zillow Inc <Z.O> is in advanced talks to buy smaller rival Trulia Inc <TRLA.N>, according to people familiar with the matter. [ID:nL4N0PZ5YK]  * Private equity firm Advent International and a Bulgarian-Russian consortium led by businessman Denis Barekov are favourites to buy Hypo Alpe Adria's Balkan bank network, two sources familiar with the process said. [ID:nL6N0PZ5QY]  * Banca Carige <CRGI.MI> has entered exclusive talks with U.S. investment fund Apollo Management Holdings LP for the sale of its two insurance units, the Italian mid-sized lender said in a statement on Thursday. [ID:nL6N0PZ640]  * Israel-based SodaStream International <SODA.O>, which makes home soda machines, is in talks to be taken private in a deal valuing the company at $828 million, Bloomberg said, citing people familiar with the matter. [ID:nL4N0PZ5NG]For the deals of the day click on [DEALS/]